    <text>
        <body>
            <div xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to István Brodarics (Brussels, 18 February
                    1533)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">Brodarics surely knows the reason why Oláh has not
                            written him in five years. What terrible times! Oláh’s loyalty to the
                            Queen has driven him here, but he misses nothing as much as his homeland
                            and his friends. He has heard that they are negotiating peace in
                            Magyaróvár, and Brodarics is one of the negotiators. He has entrusted a
                            few things to Czeglédi, he is asking him to listen to him, and if he
                            can, to assist in his affairs.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb facs="https://www.eleveltar.hu/kereso-portlet/spring/digitalcontent/getcontent/preservica/5E1CE5AD-DD07-44D7-8EDE-DD29BCFD35A2
                    "/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Ad Stephanum Brodericum episcopum Sirmiensem.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Quae causa fuerit, quod iam fere a quinquennio nihil scripserim,
                    arbitror te ipsum <add corresp="Olahus" type="insert">cogitare</add>. Temporum
                    scilicet varietas et <del corresp="Olahus">cogitare</del> partium dissensio,
                    mutuaque digladiatio. Utinam his malis Deus iam ex alto prospiceret! Mea in
                        <persName>reginam</persName> meam fides et susceptum officium me coegit, ut
                    eam hucusque sequerer et a patriae meae limitibus tam procul abessem. Ubi,
                    quamvis ex clementia Dei et munificentia principis mei nihil mihi desit, deesse
                    tamen videntur patria, <choice>
                        <orig>fatres</orig>
                        <supplied>fratres</supplied>
                    </choice>, domini et amici mei, quorum me tenet non parum desiderium. Quia autem
                    intelligam nunc pacem <placeName>Hungariae</placeName> in
                        <placeName>Owar</placeName> principibus consentientibus tractari, et te esse
                    ex arbitris unum, cuius prudentia ea tractetur.<note xml:id="note.1">Probably
                        Oláh knows it from Schepper, see Ep. 324. Cap.
                            2.<ref>olahus.tei.15330218_1</ref></note> Nonnulla is <persName>Ioannes
                        Chegledinus</persName><note xml:id="note.2">According to Ep. 325. Cap. 2,
                        this letter is a letter of mandate for
                            Czeglédi.<ref>olahus.tei.15330218_2</ref></note> provisor meus tibi meo
                    nomine referet. Rogo, velis illi fidem praestare, et res meas, si necessitas ita
                    exegerit, et curae habere et iuvare, et in illis ipsi esse adiumento, statumque
                    meum defendere. Vale.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.3"><placeName>Bruxellae</placeName> 18. Februarii 1533.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
